# Weird Schema Tags

This sample is intentionally odd. Its only job is to make the Markdoc language
server see five custom tags that come from the local sample schema.

## Moon Phase

The moon-phase tag behaves like a narrative wrapper for nocturnal release notes.
It is deliberately theatrical so completions, hover text, and validation have
something custom to work with.

{% orbit-menu course="dessert" /%}

{% $t %}

## Spice Radar

{% spice-radar heat="nebula" signal="charred-citrus" /%}

## Glitch Garden

{% glitch-garden mode="soft-chaos" season="monsoon" %}
The glitch-garden tag is for describing interfaces that should feel alive
without becoming unreadable. It gives the sample workspace a second block tag
with different attribute rules than moon-phase.
{% /glitch-garden %}

